  "title": "Marine Service Engineer",
  "description": "<ol>\n  <li>Have good knowledge of marine electronic equipment from brands such as JRC, Sailor, Furuno, Danelec, SAAB, Yokogawa, and Tokyo Keiki. At least 3–5 years of experience in the marine service field is required.</li>\n  <li>Perform Radio and VDR APT Surveys when assigned and authorized. Must hold a valid GOC (GMDSS Operator Certificate).</li>\n  <li>Carry out repair and installation tasks as assigned, with remote support when needed.</li>\n  <li>Prepare and submit detailed service, installation, or survey reports to clients or manufacturers after completing each job. Reports may be reviewed by management.</li>\n  <li>Be fully prepared for each task by collecting all necessary manuals, software, technical data, and spare parts beforehand.</li>\n  <li>Record and report accurate job hours and expenses honestly.</li>\n  <li>Follow all company safety rules and comply with MPA regulations.</li>\n  <li>Continue learning and improving skills by attending training courses or onboard training with senior engineers as arranged by the company.</li>\n</ol>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>We regret only shortlisted candidates will be contacted. All applications will be handled confidentially. By submitting your application, you agree to the collection, use, retention, and disclosure of your personal information to prospective employers.</p>\n<p>EA License No: 20C0270</p>\n<p>EA Personnel No: R22110980</p>\n<p>EA Personnel Name: Lim Hooi Mei</p>",
